OL,7,FHe came off his bike on a bend and was
OL,8,Fhit by a bike being ridden by Mark
OL,9,FTaylor.
OL,11,FIn a statement read at the inquest, Mr
OL,12,FTaylor said: "(Mr Maher-Wood's bike)
OL,13,Fseemed to have locked up and the bike
OL,14,Flaunched up in the air.
OL,16,F"It looked like a mechanical issue."
OL,18,FMr Maher-Wood was airlifted to a
OL,19,Fspecialist hospital in Lisbon but
OL,20,Fcould not be saved.
